# CODEOWNERS — composed by the harness (managed core + your local block).
# The harness owns and regenerates everything OUTSIDE the
# `codeowners.project` block on every `harness sync`; the block is yours.
#
# Syntax reference:
#   <pattern>  <@owner> [<@owner> ...]
#   Patterns follow .gitignore rules. Lines starting with # are comments.
#   The last matching rule takes precedence.
#   Owner tokens must be @username, @org/team, or user@example.com.
#
# Template placeholders (flat keys in the `templating` map of harness.config.json):
#   repo_owner         — GitHub username/org that owns the repo
#   default_codeowner  — default reviewer for all files
#   lib_codeowner      — designated reviewer for lib/ changes
#   security_codeowner — reviewer for CI + security-policy paths (.github/, .github/workflows/, SECURITY.md); defaults to default_codeowner
#   infra_codeowner    — reviewer for infrastructure paths (infra/); defaults to default_codeowner
#
# Set values in the `templating` map BEFORE running `harness sync`. Required:
# repo_owner, default_codeowner, lib_codeowner. security_codeowner and
# infra_codeowner are optional (they default to default_codeowner).

# Default: all files require review from the default codeowner.
* @{{default_codeowner}}

# lib/ changes require a dedicated reviewer.
/lib/ @{{lib_codeowner}}

# Secure-by-default: highest-risk change surfaces require codeowner review.
# CODEOWNERS is last-match-wins, so these follow the `*` default; the more
# specific /.github/workflows/ rule follows /.github/.
/.github/ @{{security_codeowner}}
/.github/workflows/ @{{security_codeowner}}
/SECURITY.md @{{security_codeowner}}
/infra/ @{{infra_codeowner}}

# harness:local-start id=codeowners.project
# Project-specific CODEOWNERS rules — preserved across `harness sync`.
# Add rules below; the harness never overwrites this block.
# harness:local-end id=codeowners.project
